    "what_description": "Macrosciadium alatum is a perennial plant species belonging to the family Apiaceae. It has a taproot and erect, biennial to perennial stems that are 1-5 cm in height. The leaves are alternate, 2-3-pinnate, and have 5-7 leaflets that are lanceolate, 1-5 cm in length, and 2-6 mm in width. The flowers are small, yellowish, and arranged in umbels, 5-10 cm in diameter, with 5-10 rays. The plant produces small, ribbed seeds in a schizocarp that is 5-10 mm in length.",
